The Objective of this lab was to Install and configure Apache HTTP Server, set up virtual hosts, and secure the web server with SSL/TLS certificates.

1. Installing and Configuring Apache HTTP Server
First I Updated the System
sudo dnf update -y
The update was successful

2.Installing Apache
sudo dnf install httpd -y

3.Start and Enable Apache
sudo systemctl start httpd
sudo systemctl enable httpd
This was a successs.

4.Configuring Firewall
sudo firewall-cmd --add-service=http --permanent
sudo firewall-cmd --reload
Firewall was enabled and actively running

5. Verifying Installation
Using http://localhost:8080 . The Apache default page was displayed succesfully

6.Website Directory and Permissions
sudo mkdir -p /var/www/html/mywebsite
sudo chown -R apache:apache /var/www/html/mywebsite

7.Test Configuration and Restart Apache
sudo apachectl configtest
sudo systemctl restart httpd

8.Virtual Hosting and Site Configuration
sudo mkdir -p /var/www/html/mywebsite1
sudo mkdir -p /var/www/html/mywebsite2

9.Creating Virtual Host Configurations
<VirtualHost *:80>
    ServerAdmin webmaster@mywebsite.com
    DocumentRoot /var/www/html/mywebsite
    ServerName mywebsite.com
    ServerAlias www.mywebsite.com
    ErrorLog /var/log/httpd/mywebsite-error.log
    CustomLog /var/log/httpd/mycoolsite-access.log combined
</VirtualHost>

10.Setting the Permissions
sudo chown -R apache:apache /var/www/html/mywebsite1
sudo chown -R apache:apache /var/www/html/mywebsite2

11.Testing Configuration and Restarting Apache
sudo apachectl configtest
sudo systemctl restart httpd
This was a success

